"title": "8845: unfruitfulness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8845: unfruitfulness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A lack of fruitfulness, whether material or spiritual, which is often seen as a sign of God's disfavour or anger.</p>\n<h2>Unfruitfulness as a moral or spiritual condition</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:19\">MAT 21:19</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:14\">MRK 11:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:32-Job15:33\">JOB 15:32–15:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:9\">EZK 17:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10-Ezek19:12\">EZK 19:10–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:43\">MAT 21:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:7-Heb6:8\">HEB 6:7–6:8</a></p>\n<h2>Reasons for unfruitfulness</h2>\n<h3>Disobedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:18-Lev26:20\">LEV 26:18–26:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:17\">DEU 11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15-Deut28:16\">DEU 28:15–28:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:46\">PSA 78:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:33-Ps107:34\">PSA 107:33–107:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:10\">ISA 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:10\">ISA 32:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:7\">HOS 8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:19\">HAG 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>A continuing preoccupation with the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:22\">MAT 13:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:19\">MRK 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14\">LUK 8:14</a></p>\n<h3>A broken relationship with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4\">JHN 15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:6\">JHN 15:6</a></p>\n<h2>Some results of unfruitfulness</h2>\n<h3>Unfruitfulness condemned</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a></p>\n<h3>Unfruitfulness leads to rejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:8-Matt3:10\">MAT 3:8–3:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:9\">LUK 3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:19\">MAT 7:19</a></p>\n<h2>Unfruitfulness retrieved</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:6-Luke13:9\">LUK 13:6–13:9</a></strong> <em>The parable holds out the possibility of restoration.</em></p>\n<h3>Discipline with a view to renewed fruitfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:2\">JHN 15:2</a></strong></p>",
